name: Absolut Native Ladies
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR269

Yes...... We’ve done it again. ChiefRocka has officially reinstated the Native Tongues crew in this simulated process print. The design features classic albums from the original members: Jungle Brothers, A Tribe Called Quest, De La Soul, Queen Latifah, Monie Love, Leaders Of The New School, Black Sheep, and Chi Ali. This t-shirt will be a great addition to the previously top selling Absolut Classics 1 and 2 tees.

name: Premo's
description:
If you're a true hip-hop head then this man needs no introduction. DJ Premier is one of the illest producers in the rap game. This dude is the truth. 
ChiefRocka Industries decided to give him his own fast food restaurant cause he's always serving us with flavor.

100% Cotton

name: Absolut Classics
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR218

It’s been close to 6 years since we introduced this design in our  season one collection 
and we’re very excited to offer it to our new customers who missed out on this gem when it debuted back in February 2004.
The design will  be printed as a simulated process print.

Absolut tried everything but they couldn't think of this one, some of hip-hop's all-time classics tapes in this beautiful Absolut Vodka theme. Only ChiefRocka can brew up something like this.WORD!

CR251

From Crooklyn’ Dodgers: Buckshot, Special Ed, and Masta Ace, to Return Of The Crooklyn’ Dodgers: Chubb Rock, O.C., Jeru da Damaga. This design will definitely break some heads. name: I Am Doom
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz
CR261

The idea for this design was thought up while watching an Adult Swim Christmas Special hosted by the Villian himself “MF DOOM” on cartoon network.We thought It’ll be cool to do the whole saturday morning cartoon theme for this design.

name: Remixes (World's Greatest)
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR267

This design has been sitting in our archives for a pretty long time and now we felt it was time to unleash the madness. Inspired by the popularity of the Remix Era, late 80’s early 90’s,  we put together a list of remixes that shook the Hip-Hop industry. From Pete Rock’s “Shut’em Down” remix, to Marley Marl’s remix of King Tee’s”At Your Own Risk” we’re  sure that this design will leave your mouth watering for more.

name: All Samples Cleared
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6OZ
CR255

Known for their humorous ryhmes and catchy hooks, Nice & Smooth were regarded as one of Hip-Hop’s greatest duo’s. Borrowing a guitar loop from Tracy Chapman’s “Fast Car”, Nice & Smooth produced a ground-breaking track called “Sometime’s I Ryhme Slow” that became a big hit. This  is the first design in our “ALL SAMPLES CLEARED” run of tees.

name: Go Indie
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR259

YOUTUBE has made it easier for us to watch any of our favorite music videos but it also started a revolution amongst independent artist who showcase their talents without the bureaucracy of the entertainment business. This t-shirt is for all those individuals out there who are standing up and letting their voices be heard. FUCK THE WHOLE INDUSTRY!

name: POPO (Protect Ya Neck)
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR253
We jacked the PUMA logo for this public service announcement. This is going out to all the crooked cops who are suppose to protect and serve all law abiding citizens, but in turn use their badge for their own reckless actions. FUCK ALL YA’LL.

name: Glazed
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 60z.
CR265

What if the creator of the Simpsons, Matt Groening, had an old school Hip-Hop special with Eric B running for president. The town of Sringfield will never be the same.

name: Bulletproof /wallets
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6OZ
CR257

ChiefRocka is paying tribute to GhostFace Killah’s “BulletProof Wallets”, an album that didn’t receive the love it deserved due to it’s mishandling by record executives. Sample clearence issues, improper track listings on the album, and poor marketing led to poor album sales. Here’s our rendition of the album title with  a plaid look of bullets and wallets.

name: Absolut Classics 2
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR249
Back by popular demand! It’s the sequel to our most popular and top selling tee “ABSOLUT CLASSICS”. In this installment we’re showcasing 2 stacks of some of our favorite rap albums of all-time. Screen-printed in a beautiful simulated process print. Get them while they’re hot!

name: Battlegrounds
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR237
When you think of the greatest M.C. battles in Hip-Hop history, nothing can come close to the M.C. Shan, Krs One battle. These two brothers set the stage for battling on wax. We all know who was the victor in this battle, but don’t get it twisted. Without Shan they’ll be no Krs!

name: Dillacious Donuts
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR241
Delicious Vinyl was a small independent record label whose roster included: Tone Loc, Young M.C., and The Pharcyde to name a few. So we decided to flip the logo and add a little flavor with none other than “THE KING OF BEATS” Jay Dee (DILLA).

name: I BOMB/ Ill verses vol.1
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR243

Inspechta Deck’s unforgettable verse on Wu tang Clan’s track “TRIUMPH” help set the tone for a true hip-hop classic. We decided to have a little fun with the design and added an interactive print on the back of the shirt. This going to be a hot one!

name: Lex, Bimerz, Benz
description:
100% COTTON / SHORT SLEEVE TEE / 6oz.
CR247

Everyone’s been doing the chain graphic tee. So we decided to turn it up a notch with this beautifully screen-printed simulated process print. Inspired by the Lost Boyz Street banger Jeeps, Lex, Bimaz, Benz. HOT!
